-- Ecuador Gets Bids for Refinery Site Preparation, BNAmericas Says
-- B y   N a t h a n   G i l l
-- 2012-05-16T19:13:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-16/ecuador-gets-bids-for-refinery-site-preparation-bnamericas-says.html
Ecuador’s government received bids
from at least 10 companies to prepare a site in the coastal
province of Manabi for the construction of an oil refinery,
Business News Americas reported.  Companies including Acciona Infraestructuras-Constructora
Nacional, China Tiesiju Civil Engineering Group, Construtora
Queiroz Galvao SA and  Sinohydro Group Ltd. (601669)  submitted offers for
contract, estimated to be worth $315 million, the Santiago-based
 news agency  said today on its  website . Ecuador will announce the
winner on June 8, BNAmericas said.  Ecuador’s Non-Renewable Natural Resources Ministry’s press
office declined to comment about the bids today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nathan Gill in Quito at 
 ngill4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
